# LLM Wiki Context Rule

Before answering project questions or editing code, start with
`docs/llm-wiki/00-agent-entrypoint.md`.

Use the wiki as an index, not as bulk context:

- Read the entrypoint first.
- Pick only one topic page for the task.
- Use `docs/llm-wiki/indexes/files-by-feature.md` or
  `docs/llm-wiki/indexes/symbols-by-feature.md` to identify exact source files.
- Search by route, endpoint, symbol, selector, CSS class, algorithm name, or
  result key before opening files.
- Open broad folders, large mapper files, templates, or styles only when the
  task is complex or a targeted lookup is inconclusive.

Do not duplicate the wiki in Cursor rules. Keep this rule short so it stays cheap
to include in every Cursor chat.
